ring" label="Author's Name" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">Writer: Kim Summers</Author><BodyCopy type="dhtml" label="Body Copy" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" Height=""><![CDATA[<p>Take one summer, 60 teens, and a brightly lit stage and you have the first annual Brigham Young University-Idaho Theatre Summer Camp, designed to help participants develop their theatrical talent.</p>
<p><br />The weeklong camp (Aug. 1-6) includes classes in improvisation, corrective and gore make-up classes, voice diction, set design, light and sound and many more. The camp will also host a dance and mystery dinner that will help participants get into the spirit of performing. Applicants will showcase their skills at the end of the week in a revue-style performance for their friends and family.</p>
